  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN) regulations\n\n3. Prevention Mechanisms\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Corporate and individual sanctions\n\n5. Reporting Requirements\n- Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n- Suspicious activity reports\n- Cross-border currency transfer declarations\n\n6. Regulatory Oversight\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n7. Compliance Obligations\n- Financial institutions' internal control systems\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Staff training programs\n- Regular audit and verification processes\n\nThis framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
